# Release-time supply-chain scan (release-reusable.yml `semgrep` step).
# Pinned to current stable to maximise rule coverage at tag-cut time.
# Drift from semgrep-review/requirements.in is intentional (see
# release-reusable.yml comment for the asymmetric-pin policy).
#
# Regenerate the locked requirements.txt on Python 3.14 (matches the
# `actions/setup-python` version pinned in the workflows that consume
# this lock):
#   python3.14 -m venv .tmp/pip-compile-venv
#   .tmp/pip-compile-venv/bin/pip install pip-tools
#   .tmp/pip-compile-venv/bin/pip-compile \
#     --generate-hashes --strip-extras --allow-unsafe \
#     --output-file=.github/requirements/semgrep-release/requirements.txt \
#     .github/requirements/semgrep-release/requirements.in
# Unpinned on purpose — see the validate lock's requirements.in for why a `==`
# here breaks Dependabot's pip-compile bump path (#186). Unlike the review pin,
# this one is meant to track current stable, so Dependabot bumping the lock is
# exactly the intent.
semgrep
